There are even children who don’t want to be associated with their mothers online because they don’t want to be ostracised or lose face for being born of a divorced woman. Sex dolls or Siri dolls are often more accepted in Thai society than divorced women are.

Divorcees are expected to bear the brunt of the emotional and spiritual pain from a failed marriage and fix themselves before returning to society. Men are often expected to continue working and carrying out their traditional male duties in Thailand because a wife doesn’t work as well in Thai society. Women, on the other hand, can be seen as less fully feminine and thus not offered marriage prospects after a failed marriage unfortunately.

A typical Thai family consists of the mother, father and children and is an undeniable part of children’s lives in Thai society. An increased divorce rate means that more Thai children have to face growing up without one parent in the family home.

If there are divorced parents in a family, they have to set a great example to their children by maintaining a functional, loving relationship in front of their children.
